<text>How Does a Crystal Grow?
p. 3 of 8
Many manufacturers grow crystals for their industries.  But in order to do this effectively, they have to know how to harness the forces that hold them together and allow them to grow. You have seen how atoms in crystals relate to their neighbors.  Now you can discover how close atoms need to be in order to be added to a crystal.
 
     
1. While the model is running, click  and watch what happens to the atom added from a distance. 
2. Now, while the model is still running, click   and watch the second atom. 
3. Reset the model by clicking the BACK button of the player. Check the box under the model frame, and then run the model and follow steps 2,3 once again while it is running.&#10112; 
4. What can you conclude about the attractions among atoms and how they contribute to crystal growth?
 


&#10112; Adapted from page designed by Dalit Levy for the TELS project.

   

</text>
